      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_54gc' title='Col. 54GC &mdash; HL Deb 19 July 2004 vol 664 c54GC' name='column_54gc' href='#column_54gc' rel='bookmark'>54GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01168'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_421' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 122 [<span class="italic">Board's duty where application or notification received under section 121</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01169'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_422' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Baroness Hollis of Heigham</span> moved Amendments Nos. 193A to 193C:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01170'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_423' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 84, line 17, after "effect" insert "(a "scheme failure notice")"
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01171'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_424' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 84, line 19, leave out "withdrawal notice" and insert "notice to that effect (a "withdrawal notice")"
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01172'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_425' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 84, line 33, leave out subsection (6) and insert&#x2014;
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01173'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_426' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        "(6) For the purposes of this Part a notice issued under subsection (2) or (3) is not binding until&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the period within which the issue of the notice may be reviewed by virtue of Chapter 6 has expired, and</li>
        <li>(b) if the issue of the notice is so reviewed&#x2014;</li>
        <ol>
        <li>(i) the review and any reconsideration.</li>
        <li>(ii) any reference to the PPF Ombudsman in respect of the issue of the notice, and</li>
        <li>(iii) any appeal against his determination or directions,</li>
        </ol>
        </ol>
        has been finally disposed of and the notice has not been revoked, varied or substituted.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01174'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_427' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (7) Where a notice issued under subsection (2) or (3) becomes binding, the Board must as soon as reasonably practicable give a notice to that effect together with a copy of the binding notice to&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the Regulator,</li>
        <li>(b) the trustees or managers of the scheme, and</li>
        <li>(c) the employer.</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01175'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_428' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (8) Notices under this section must be in the prescribed form and contain such information as may be prescribed.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01176'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_429' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (9) A notice given under subsection (7) in relation to a withdrawal notice under subsection (2) which has become binding must state the time from which the Board ceases to be involved with the scheme (see section 140)."
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-01177'>
